{"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpConnectionRef\/close(cancellable:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpConnectionRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpConnectionRef\/IOStreamProtocol-Implementations"]]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Closes the stream, releasing resources related to it. This will also"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"close the individual input and output streams, if they are not already"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"closed.","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:3GIO16IOStreamProtocolPAAE5close11cancellableSbAA14CancellableRefVSg_tKF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO16TcpConnectionRefV","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","title":"close(cancellable:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"close","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"role":"symbol","extendedModule":"GIO"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/tcpconnectionref\/close(cancellable:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"close","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once the stream is closed, all other operations will return"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"closed"},{"type":"text","text":". Closing a stream multiple times will not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"return an error.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Closing a stream will automatically flush any outstanding buffers","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the stream."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Streams will be automatically closed when the last reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is dropped, but you might want to call this function to make sure"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"resources are released as early as possible.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some streams might keep the backing store of the stream (e.g. a file"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"descriptor) open after the stream is closed. See the documentation for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the individual stream for details."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On failure the first error that happened will be reported, but the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"close operation will finish as much as possible. A stream that failed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to close will still return "},{"code":"closed","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for all operations."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Still, it is important to check and report the error to the user,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"otherwise there might be a loss of data as all data might not be written.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"code":"cancellable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is not NULL, then the operation can be cancelled by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"triggering the cancellable object from another thread. If the operation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"was cancelled, the error "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancelled"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Cancelling a close will still leave the stream closed, but some streams"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can use a faster close that doesn’t block to e.g. check errors."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of this method just calls close on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"individual input\/output streams.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableRef":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableref","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" allows operations to be cancelled."}],"title":"CancellableRef"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TcpConnectionRef/close(cancellable:)":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpConnectionRef\/close(cancellable:)","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"close"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV"},{"text":"?) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tcpconnectionref\/close(cancellable:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Closes the stream, releasing resources related to it. This will also"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"close the individual input and output streams, if they are not already","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"closed.","type":"text"}],"title":"close(cancellable:)"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TcpConnectionRef/IOStreamProtocol-Implementations":{"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tcpconnectionref\/iostreamprotocol-implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpConnectionRef\/IOStreamProtocol-Implementations","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","title":"IOStreamProtocol Implementations","type":"topic","abstract":[]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TcpConnectionRef":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TcpConnectionRef","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tcpconnectionref","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"This is the subclass of [class","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketConnection","isActive":true},{"text":"] that is created","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for TCP\/IP sockets.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpConnectionRef","title":"TcpConnectionRef","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TcpConnectionRef","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SocketConnection":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SocketConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SocketConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketConnection","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socketconnection","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocketConnection"},{"type":"text","text":" is a [class"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOStream","isActive":true},{"text":"] for a connected socket. They","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"can be created either by [class"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketClient","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] when connecting to a host,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"or by [class","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketListener","type":"reference"},{"text":"] when accepting a new client.","type":"text"}],"title":"SocketConnection"}}}